I threw that in there as a deliberate allusion to the paradox in my own beliefs.  Not as an indicator of religious inclination.<br>
<br>
I have very little faith in my own convictions, yet somehow, I also live by them.  This makes me somewhat aware (when I squint and twist my face all up) that my own perception of my perceptions is in itself hypocritical.  <br>
<br>
So, don't for a second think that I have any idea what to believe in this world.  But sometimes, I forget and live like I do, anyway.<br>
