<br>
Once upon a time, there were these bearskin clad savages, who had no idea what caused things to happen around them.  Seeing as they had evolved this silly little peice of tissue called a cerebral cortex some time in the not so distant past, they were able to formulate thoughts such as &quot;What made that big booming sound after that light flashed in the distance?&quot; and &quot;Why is the sky blue?&quot;.  No one knew the answer, yet everyone wondered.  And it scared them that they didnt know the answer.  Knowing the answer makes everything seem ok.<br>
<br>
One day while sitting around the fire, the old topic of &quot;Why is the sky blue?&quot; was tossed out by a youngster.  Instead of it being a rhetorical kind of question, and everyone just sitting there staring at the fire, a member of the tribe, lets call him Reverend Graak, replied &quot;Why, the sky was made by this mysterious super being, called .. ummm, God, yeah thats the ticket!~  God.&quot;<br>
<br>
The people around the fire had never heard of such a thing.  Perhaps it was true.  It made sense, the guessed.  Perhaps everything unknown was a work of god.  This felt very comforting to the bearskin clad savages.  Endorphines flooded their brains, giving them that feeling of 'everything was now ok'.  They had the answer to everything.  Every time there was a question that no one knew the answer to, Reverend Graak would reply, &quot;Tis the work of God!&quot;.<br>
<br>
People took great comfort in this crutch to their mental well being.  They regarded Reverend Graak as a man of great wisdom (when in actuality, he just made up a story).  The people took great care of Reverend Graak, for he was the man who opened their eyes to God!<br>
<br>
As the years passed, Reverend Graak gained more and more social power, and had many children.  All of his energy needs were taken care of by the members of his tribe giving him, and his offspring, for he was the messenger of God.  As his children grew, Reverend Graak told his children that if they too spread the word of God, they too will have to do only this, to receive food (energy), power, and status.  It was quite a scam this Reverend Graak had come across.<br>
<br>
Of course, others around Reverend Graak were jealous of what they saw, for he had to do nothing, and received everything he needed to have strong, successful offspring.  Being ANIMALS themselves, they want nothing but that same thing for their offspring.  They realized that Graak, a guy they grew up with, had never spoken of this God until that one night....  BING! ...  On went the proverbial lightbulb.  Perhaps if they made up a story too, something like, &quot;Hey, there is this 'other' god that causes fire&quot; or &quot;Each star in the sky is a God&quot;, etc etc, that they too would gain energy, power, and status.  The people of the bearskin clad tribe took great comfort in these stories also.  They showered this second man with all he needed to build power and have many successful offspring.<br>
<br>
So, as the generations passed, the concept of God was just something that always 'was'.  For you see, they did not even conceive of the notion that there were actually people, at some point in the past, who had not conceived of the notion of God , or Gods.  For you see, the world would just be a SCARY place if you couldnt explain everything with God.  The people who spread the knowledge (errr made up stories) of what these God(s) do, where they live, where they come from, what they look like, etc, continued to lead successful lives, producing many successful children, who in turn, have children, who in turn have children........ <br>
<br>
So you see, religeon is a survival strategy.  Were it NOT a successful strategy, ie. it didnt bring in the energy required  to survive and produce successful offspring, it simply would NOT have survived past Reverend Graak.  Life is all about strategies in energy aquisition.  Religeon has proven VERY profitable, as it takes 0 energy to prove what you say, yet you can make a living off of it.  Good deal, ecologically speaking.  Good on Reverend Graak.  <br>
<br>
<br>
The End <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utoekpet966.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toekpet966</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/26/02 10:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=378>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Tokepot, I know you personally and know that youve smoked weed and still would like to. Have you any idea the mass amount of murders that have been commited over drugs?<br>
